## Option Key not detected

It turns out that the **Option (or Alt) ⌥** key on macOS is currently not working for [`ShortcutActivator`](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/ShortcutActivator-class.html) on macOS **on web**.

That is, any `shortcuts` that use the alt key do not work. That applies both to `SingleActivator` as well as `LogicalKeySet`; [`LogicalKeyboardKey.alt`](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/services/LogicalKeyboardKey/shift-constant.html) simply seems to be broken. This happens to our users on Chrome using Macbook.

---

```dart
SingleActivator(
  LogicalKeyboardKey.keyA,
)
```

Is detected but:

```dart
SingleActivator(
  LogicalKeyboardKey.keyA,
  alt: true,
)
```

is not detected on macOS on web. All the other modifiers still work.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Run `flutter create bug --platforms=web`.
2. Update `main.dart` as follows:

<details><summary>Click to expand code snippet</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/services.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Shift is broken',
      shortcuts: const {
        SingleActivator(
          LogicalKeyboardKey.keyA,
          control: true,
        ): PrintIntent(false),
        SingleActivator(
          LogicalKeyboardKey.keyA,
          alt: true,
        ): PrintIntent(true),
      },
      actions: {
        PrintIntent: CallbackAction<PrintIntent>(onInvoke: (intent) {
          if (intent.alt) {
            // This is never called.
            print('Alt is working');
            return;
          }
          print('Control is working.');
        }),
      },
      builder: (context, child) {
        return const Focus(
          autofocus: true,
          child: Placeholder(),
        );
      },
    );
  }
}

class PrintIntent extends Intent {
  const PrintIntent(this.alt);

  final bool alt;
}
```

</details>

3. Run `cd bug` and `flutter run -d chrome` on macOS.
4. Focus the window.
5. Press CTRL + A.
6. Press OPTION + A.

**Expected results:** `Control is working.` and then `Alt is working.`

**Actual results:** `Control is working.` only.

